markets.title: Will the rate of core PCE inflation be above 0.4% in September 2025?
markets.rules_primary: If the (single-decimal) month-over-month percent change in the Personal Consumption Expenditures Price Index excluding food and energy is above 0.4% in September 2025 according to the Bureau of Economic Analysis, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The market will close at 8:25 AM ET on the expected release of the data. It will expire at the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of the data, or one week after the expected release of the data.
